                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12935664" author="michaelsembwever" created="Thu, 25 Nov 2010 07:34:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem was the list of mutations inside the Map&amp;lt;ByteBuffer, Map&amp;lt;String, List&amp;lt;Mutation&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; that is sent to batch_mutate(..) isn&apos;t appended to, instead it was overridden.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch allows subsequent mutations (under the same columnFamily and key) to be appended to the existing list.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12935804" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 25 Nov 2010 17:24:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the fix!  Committed w/ minor change to emphasize that subBatch is only created once.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12935907" author="karthick" created="Thu, 25 Nov 2010 23:19:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970406" author="hudson" created="Sat, 11 Dec 2010 07:35:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.7 #70 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/70/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/70/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
